<TITLE> BCL damages six vehicles in Ctg </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, May 3 (bdnews24.com)  BCL activists of Chittagong University attacked and damaged six private buses which were taking students to the campus on Monday, injuring three drivers and two passengers. The Bangladesh Chhatra League has been observing an indefinite strike on the campus since Apr 16 protesting the death of a fellow activist. The BCL activists hurled stones and brickbats at the buses operated by the company Tori in the city's Muradpur and Sholoshahar at around 10am, said Taslima Akhter, sub-inspector of Panchlaish police station. Police arrested two activists, Kaiser Ferdous and Shahidul Islam, she said. Among the injured the condition of a driver, Jashimuddin, who has been admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital, is critical. Others received first aid. The university's assistant proctor Chandan Kumar Poddar said the situation of the campus is normal, with classes and examinations taking place and the shuttle trains running.. 
